1
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:10,125
[MAYA] And now, I shall
hereby hand down my verdict!

2
00:00:10,208 --> 00:00:12,708
I find the defendant,
super guilty!

3
00:00:12,791 --> 00:00:15,625
No! If only I had
an Ace Attorney to help!

4
00:00:15,708 --> 00:00:17,291
[PHOENIX]
Objection!

5
00:00:17,375 --> 00:00:18,791
[MAYA]
Who is that?

6
00:00:18,875 --> 00:00:20,666
[PHOENIX] A man who
believes in his clients.

7
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:22,916
And will strike down
any evildoers!

8
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,458
Lawyer Samurai,
Phoenix Wright enters the fray!

9
00:00:27,541 --> 00:00:29,208
Sally Forth!

10
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:31,125
Going to court, you say?

11
00:00:31,208 --> 00:00:33,458
Call Wright and
company right away!

12
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:38,500
[PHOENIX groans]

13
00:00:38,583 --> 00:00:40,166
[MAYA]
Hmm. Nope.

14
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:42,625
One more time!
With some feeling!

15
00:00:42,708 --> 00:00:44,541
[groans]
Do we have to?

16
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:45,791
You bet!

17
00:00:45,875 --> 00:00:47,416
We're not stopping until
we get the perfect take.

18
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:48,916
--[stomach growling]
--[BOTH gasp]

19
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,208
[MAYA]
Well, maybe after a snack.

20
00:00:51,291 --> 00:00:53,416
[PHOENIX]
I'm not cut out for showbiz.

21
00:02:25,666 --> 00:02:27,916
Huh? You're really
gonna stop filming?

22
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:31,458
[coughs] I think we should
try exploring other avenues

23
00:02:31,541 --> 00:02:32,666
to get the word out.

24
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:34,250
I get ya.

25
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:36,333
You just don't feel like the
Lawyer Samurai character works.

26
00:02:36,416 --> 00:02:38,958
--Well...
--How's this for an idea?

27
00:02:39,041 --> 00:02:41,166
A new character, called
the Lawyer General.

28
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:43,000
You're completely
missing the issue here.

29
00:02:43,083 --> 00:02:44,750
[ <i>Signal Samurai</i> theme plays]

30
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:46,250
[gasps]
It's your song!

31
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,166
The <i>Signal Samurai</i> theme!

32
00:02:48,250 --> 00:02:50,083
Reminds me of when I was a kid.

33
00:02:50,166 --> 00:02:52,833
That was your favorite right?
You still have the figures.

34
00:02:52,916 --> 00:02:55,291
Radio, huh?

35
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:57,375
[MAYA]
Hmm? What's on your mind?

36
00:02:57,458 --> 00:03:00,375
Oh. I just kind of
have a thing for radio.

37
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:03,125
[MAYA] Really? I bet
there's a story behind that!

38
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:04,250
[PHOENIX]
Hmm.

39
00:03:06,083 --> 00:03:09,333
[PHOENIX] Well, it all started
when I was in middle school.

40
00:03:09,416 --> 00:03:11,500
[PHOENIX hums]

41
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:14,125
[BUTZ]
Yo!

42
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:18,041
Hey, man.

43
00:03:18,125 --> 00:03:19,625
Hey, Nick.

44
00:03:19,708 --> 00:03:22,625
So, did you watch
<i>Rainbow Samurai</i> yesterday?

45
00:03:22,708 --> 00:03:23,708
[BUTZ]
Huh?

46
00:03:23,791 --> 00:03:25,625
Take down evil
with colorful justice!

47
00:03:25,708 --> 00:03:28,541
No way. I told ya,
I grew out of that kid's stuff

48
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,541
after Signal Samurai.

49
00:03:30,625 --> 00:03:32,916
What a buzzkill.

50
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,583
Yeah, yeah whatever.

51
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:37,583
Radio's my jam.
Grown-ups only.

52
00:03:37,666 --> 00:03:39,708
You don't say.

53
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:41,875
[DEE] Sending you some good
vibes while you grab some

54
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:45,166
quick bites, it's your portable
lunch date, Delicious Dee.

55
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:48,000
She's sweet and yummy.

56
00:03:48,083 --> 00:03:50,000
[DEE] Watch out for this
track 'cause it's spicy!

57
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:52,875
Hold the wasabi and taste
the fire through the airways.

58
00:03:52,958 --> 00:03:54,250
Aw, yeah!

59
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:56,750
So, this is you
being an adult, huh?

60
00:03:58,416 --> 00:04:02,000
[BUTZ]
Hm? You dropped something, bro.

61
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:03,583
[PHOENIX gasps ]

62
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:06,375
I can't believe you still carry
that dinky little thing around.

63
00:04:06,458 --> 00:04:07,625
Yeah, well...

64
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:09,541
I'd bet my life ol'
Edgy-boy's thrown his

65
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:11,416
in the trash by now.

66
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,041
Sounds like something he'd do.

67
00:04:16,125 --> 00:04:17,833
After all, he transferred
without telling us

68
00:04:17,916 --> 00:04:19,083
how to keep in contact.

69
00:04:19,166 --> 00:04:21,416
I don't think it's fair
to blame him for that!

70
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:23,375
When you think about
what happened to him.

71
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:25,750
Yeah, you're
not wrong, but still.

72
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:27,125
[PHOENIX]
Three years ago.

73
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:29,083
There was a horrible murder
that actually happened

74
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:31,250
inside the courthouse!

75
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:35,500
The victim was Miles' father.
A prominent defense attorney.

76
00:04:35,583 --> 00:04:37,458
With nobody left to call family,

77
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:39,958
Miles had to move out of town.

78
00:04:40,041 --> 00:04:43,708
We haven't heard so much
as a word from him since.

79
00:04:43,791 --> 00:04:45,916
We still don't know
who killed his dad.

80
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,916
But whoever it was
left him to die alone.

81
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,708
[PHOENIX] Wherever Miles is,
I hope he's okay.

82
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:54,250
[BUTZ]
Yeah me, too.

83
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:56,375
And I hope his li'l
pup is doing well.

84
00:05:02,958 --> 00:05:07,333
[MISSILE yipping]

85
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:14,250
[MISSILE pants]

86
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:15,458
[MILES]
Uh...

87
00:05:15,541 --> 00:05:16,541
[MISSILE barks]

88
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:19,125
Cool. Right? He looks like Papa.

89
00:05:19,208 --> 00:05:20,916
Why'd you go and dress him up?

90
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:23,125
Well, because...

91
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:24,708
...I thought it would
make you smile.

92
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:26,166
[gasps]

93
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:29,041
[gasps] I think this cravat
suits him better, though.

94
00:05:29,125 --> 00:05:31,500
[MISSILE whines]

95
00:05:31,583 --> 00:05:33,833
[FRANZISKA]
Hey! Don't go! Come back!

96
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,000
[sighs]

97
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,708
[pants, barks]

98
00:05:43,791 --> 00:05:44,875
[FRANZISKA yelps]

99
00:05:44,958 --> 00:05:46,791
[NARRATOR]
Yo, yo, yo!

100
00:05:46,875 --> 00:05:49,583
Seven blades of justice,
each a different shade!

101
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:53,166
[RAINBOW SAMURAI]
We are the Rainbow Samurai!

102
00:05:55,916 --> 00:05:57,125
[FRANZISKA]
That's so lame.

103
00:05:59,083 --> 00:06:00,791
[MISSILE pants]

104
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:08,250
[KARMA]
Hm?

105
00:06:11,708 --> 00:06:14,166
I'm glad you're home, Papa.

106
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:15,791
[MILES]
Welcome back, sir.

107
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:16,875
[KARMA]
Hm.

108
00:06:24,375 --> 00:06:25,541
How was court today?

109
00:06:25,625 --> 00:06:28,083
I'm sure you won,
like you always do, right?

110
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:29,333
But of course.

111
00:06:29,416 --> 00:06:30,916
That's because you're the best!

112
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:35,083
Some day, I'm going to be
a prosecutor, like you.

113
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:36,625
Obviously.

114
00:06:36,708 --> 00:06:38,791
Will you follow in your
father's footsteps?

115
00:06:38,875 --> 00:06:42,416
[MILES gasps]
Oh. I'm not quite sure.

116
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,041
I know.

117
00:06:44,125 --> 00:06:46,916
Why don't you take Miles to one
of your trials sometime, Papa?

118
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,875
Oh. He doesn't have to.

119
00:06:48,958 --> 00:06:50,416
Consider it done.

120
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,000
[FRANZISKA]
Yay! In that case,

121
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:53,333
I'd like to go with you--

122
00:06:53,416 --> 00:06:55,333
there's something I really
want to do afterwards!

123
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:09,166
[MILES]
I miss you...

124
00:07:10,583 --> 00:07:12,708
[KARMA] Let's get to work
on this orphanage deal.

125
00:07:12,791 --> 00:07:14,791
I'll be sending
Miles there soon.

126
00:07:16,416 --> 00:07:20,541
[groans]
That damned old wound.

127
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:23,166
You're still trying to get in
my way, aren't you, Edgeworth?

128
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:25,041
Even beyond the grave.

129
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:37,083
Let him go!
Don't hurt my father!

130
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:38,833
[gunshot]

131
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:40,833
[KARMA bellows]

132
00:07:43,166 --> 00:07:44,583
[gasps]

133
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:49,291
[MISSILE whines]

134
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:55,791
[DEE]
So what's on today's lunch menu?

135
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:57,375
I'm being bad and
having jelly donuts.

136
00:07:57,458 --> 00:07:58,708
Yum, yum, yum, yum.

137
00:07:58,791 --> 00:08:00,833
Yum-my!

138
00:08:03,541 --> 00:08:05,375
[PHOENIX]
Cutting class, I see.

139
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:09,833
[DEE] All right, my Dee-vo-tees,
this one is a special request!

140
00:08:09,916 --> 00:08:12,875
[PHOENIX]
Yes! That's it!

141
00:08:12,958 --> 00:08:15,083
This is how we can
get in touch with Miles!

142
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:16,416
Huh?

143
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,083
[PHOENIX chuckles]

144
00:08:18,166 --> 00:08:20,500
[LAWYER growls]
This wasn't in discovery.

145
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,208
I object!

146
00:08:22,291 --> 00:08:23,916
[KARMA] It's your fault
for not being thorough

147
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,375
in your investigation.

148
00:08:25,458 --> 00:08:28,125
Von Karma is
meticulousness personified.

149
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:30,250
But you are a subpar attorney.

150
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:33,583
Don't forget: Someone's
life is in your hands.

151
00:08:35,875 --> 00:08:37,458
Guilty!

152
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:39,541
[CROWD cheering]

153
00:08:39,625 --> 00:08:41,208
[gasps]

154
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,708
[EDGEWORTH] Von Karma's
an extraordinary attorney.

155
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:46,250
But, aren't prosecutors
your enemies?

156
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,583
That's not how I look at it.

157
00:08:48,666 --> 00:08:51,458
We fight each other, sure,
but to find the truth.

158
00:08:51,541 --> 00:08:53,791
At the end of the day, it's
both our jobs to make sure

159
00:08:53,875 --> 00:08:55,958
evil is punished.

160
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:58,416
Or at least, that's
how it should be.

161
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:06,291
Incredible work.
Would you like to comment?

162
00:09:06,375 --> 00:09:08,625
[REPORTER B] Your perfect
record remains intact!

163
00:09:08,708 --> 00:09:10,875
I don't care about my record.

164
00:09:10,958 --> 00:09:14,166
I fight for justice.
That's my duty.

165
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:16,166
[FRANZISKA] Papa never
lets any criminals get away.

166
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:17,833
He always wins!

167
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:20,416
He's basically a superhero.

168
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:23,000
I can't wait to grow up
and be just like him.

169
00:09:23,083 --> 00:09:25,041
Maybe I'll even get
to be his partner.

170
00:09:27,041 --> 00:09:29,500
[FRANZISKA]
Papa!

171
00:09:29,583 --> 00:09:31,791
Your case was
absolutely perfect.

172
00:09:31,875 --> 00:09:33,208
[KARMA]
Naturally.

173
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:34,875
Brilliant cross-examining.

174
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:37,375
If only your father
had been my opponent.

175
00:09:37,458 --> 00:09:39,750
Then I might actually
have enjoyed myself.

176
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:42,000
[gasps]

177
00:09:42,083 --> 00:09:45,000
Why don't the
two of you wait in the car.

178
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,291
'Kay!

179
00:09:53,375 --> 00:09:55,750
[FRANZISKA gasps]

180
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:57,125
[MISSILE barks]

181
00:09:57,208 --> 00:09:58,875
Can you spare some
change for these dogs?

182
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:00,833
A little goes a long way!

183
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:04,250
Hey, come on! Let's shop.

184
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:05,625
[MILES]
Sure.

185
00:10:08,666 --> 00:10:10,916
[FRANZISKA] I think this
place is huge overseas.

186
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,875
But there's only one in Japan.

187
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:16,458
Whaddaya think?
The red one or the blue one?

188
00:10:16,541 --> 00:10:18,333
Uh. I dunno.

189
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:20,166
Well. In that case...

190
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:21,708
...I'll go with the red one.

191
00:10:21,791 --> 00:10:25,000
It's almost the same
color as your vest!

192
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:27,708
Oh! Papa! Look at these!

193
00:10:27,791 --> 00:10:29,500
[MISSILE barks]

194
00:10:29,583 --> 00:10:32,000
[FRANZISKA gasps]
Wait! Come back!

195
00:10:32,083 --> 00:10:33,958
Stay here. I'll go get him.

196
00:10:34,041 --> 00:10:35,750
Sure. Please hurry!

197
00:10:39,958 --> 00:10:41,750
Missile! C'mere!

198
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:45,583
[gasps]

199
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,375
Please, forgive me.

200
00:10:51,541 --> 00:10:53,916
[GOLDY]
Hmph! What a rude boy.

201
00:11:01,875 --> 00:11:03,541
[DEE]
Now for some serious news.

202
00:11:03,625 --> 00:11:05,333
A little poor doggo's
gotten lost in

203
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:07,583
the Lordly Tailor Shopping Mall.

204
00:11:07,666 --> 00:11:09,750
Lordly Tailor? Wait, here?

205
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:12,291
[DEE] Her name is Napalm,
and she's a white Pomeranian

206
00:11:12,375 --> 00:11:14,125
wearing a cute
little pink ribbon.

207
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:17,250
The heart-shaped spot on her
belly makes her extra special!

208
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:19,750
The owner's really
worried about her.

209
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:23,333
Wait, is this right?
There's a 5,000 dollar reward?

210
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:27,541
I guess my dog's not the
only troublemaker here today.

211
00:11:27,625 --> 00:11:29,708
[DEE] Anyway,
here's a special request.

212
00:11:29,791 --> 00:11:33,208
[Signal Samurai theme plays

213
00:11:33,291 --> 00:11:35,083
Signal Samurai?

214
00:11:35,166 --> 00:11:40,416
[theme continues to play]

215
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:41,833
You guys...

216
00:11:41,916 --> 00:11:45,166
I want to become a defense
lawyer, just like my dad.

217
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:47,708
[gasps]
You'd be amazing!

218
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:50,791
I can't wait to watch
you battle in court!

219
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:52,083
[gasps]

220
00:11:54,583 --> 00:11:57,000
I can't wait to grow up
and be just like him.

221
00:11:57,083 --> 00:11:59,000
Maybe I'll even get
to be his partner.

222
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:03,125
If only your father
had been my opponent.

223
00:12:03,208 --> 00:12:05,541
Then I might actually
have enjoyed myself.

224
00:12:08,083 --> 00:12:10,625
[MILES]
Father. What should I do?

225
00:12:12,416 --> 00:12:13,875
[DEE]
What a catchy throwback.

226
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:16,750
That's a request coming
to you from Signal Blue.

227
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:17,791
[MILES gasps]

228
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:19,208
[DEE]
Oh, wow, cool!

229
00:12:19,291 --> 00:12:21,541
It even comes with
a heartfelt message.

230
00:12:21,625 --> 00:12:23,833
Signal Red.
Hope you're doin' well.

231
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:25,500
We miss you.

232
00:12:25,583 --> 00:12:26,958
[DEE, PHOENIX]
And your puppy, too.

233
00:12:27,041 --> 00:12:28,583
[PHOENIX] I really wish
we were all together

234
00:12:28,666 --> 00:12:31,041
playing Signal Samurai again.

235
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:33,083
I know you had to
move away suddenly,

236
00:12:33,166 --> 00:12:35,083
but know it doesn't
matter where you live.

237
00:12:35,166 --> 00:12:38,000
I've always got your back
and am rooting for you.

238
00:12:38,083 --> 00:12:39,541
We'll meet again one day.

239
00:12:39,625 --> 00:12:41,833
I know it.

240
00:12:41,916 --> 00:12:43,500
That was you, Wright?

241
00:12:43,583 --> 00:12:45,958
[DEE] I hope Red and
Blue meet again, too!

242
00:12:46,041 --> 00:12:48,208
Darlin' Dee's
cheering for you two!

243
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,833
You never change, do you?

244
00:12:49,916 --> 00:12:51,041
I'm glad.

245
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:53,250
[MISSILE barks]

246
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:54,375
[MILES gasps]

247
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:59,125
[NAPALM whines]

248
00:12:59,208 --> 00:13:01,666
I see. So that's
why you ran away.

249
00:13:03,791 --> 00:13:06,291
[MILES] A white Pomeranian
wearing a ribbon.

250
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:10,416
You must be Napalm, right?

251
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:13,916
[GOLDY]
Ah. There's my widdle baby.

252
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,208
[MILES gasps]

253
00:13:15,291 --> 00:13:17,250
I looked all over for you.

254
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:19,375
You naughty little pup.

255
00:13:25,375 --> 00:13:26,458
[FRANZISKA sighs]

256
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:29,291
What's wrong?

257
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:32,625
We came all the way here
so you could eat pancakes.

258
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:33,750
I know.

259
00:13:36,958 --> 00:13:40,041
But... I want to wait for Miles.

260
00:13:40,125 --> 00:13:43,375
Thank you so much
for finding my precious girl.

261
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:47,041
I'm Goldy. And that fluffy
nugget is my bad dog.

262
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:49,125
Ah. You're the owner?

263
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:50,333
Thank goodness.

264
00:13:50,416 --> 00:13:53,500
Oh, yes. I was
so worried about her.

265
00:13:53,583 --> 00:13:55,791
[NAPALM growls]

266
00:13:55,875 --> 00:13:57,333
Oh, she's playing.

267
00:13:57,416 --> 00:14:00,416
She's mad that her mama lost
track of her while shopping.

268
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:02,166
[MILES]
Yeah. Seems like it.

269
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:03,583
I never did have kids.

270
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:07,708
So. You know, I may have
spoiled her because of that.

271
00:14:07,791 --> 00:14:11,083
--[NAPALM growls]
--It's okay. Come to Mommy.

272
00:14:11,166 --> 00:14:13,041
Get over here!

273
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:15,458
Poor dear. She's rattled.

274
00:14:15,541 --> 00:14:17,875
I guess I'll have to give
her some extra treats.

275
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:19,708
[laughs]

276
00:14:19,791 --> 00:14:21,666
We're leaving, Napalm.

277
00:14:21,750 --> 00:14:22,958
[NAPALM barks]

278
00:14:23,041 --> 00:14:24,500
It doesn't sound
like she's happy

279
00:14:24,583 --> 00:14:25,708
to be going with you.

280
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:27,125
Is that right?

281
00:14:27,208 --> 00:14:29,541
So, you think you know
better than her mother, then.

282
00:14:29,625 --> 00:14:31,458
I don't mean
to sound rude, ma'am.

283
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:34,125
But are you certain that
you're the owner of this dog?

284
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:36,083
Why would I lie about that?

285
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:37,500
[MILES]
I'm sorry.

286
00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:39,958
But something about this
situation is making me uneasy.

287
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:43,041
I see. You're trying
to steal my dog?

288
00:14:43,125 --> 00:14:45,791
I knew you looked
like a delinquent.

289
00:14:45,875 --> 00:14:47,083
[MILES]
What was that?

290
00:14:47,166 --> 00:14:48,291
[FRANZISKA gasps]

291
00:14:50,208 --> 00:14:51,208
Miles--

292
00:14:54,166 --> 00:14:55,708
Here's a bit of advice.

293
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:57,416
You've got an ugly mutt already.

294
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:00,250
If you know what's good for you,
you'll take him and leave now.

295
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:01,333
[MISSILE barks]

296
00:15:01,416 --> 00:15:02,500
Do you have proof
that she's yours?

297
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:04,833
[laughs]
Proof. Sure.

298
00:15:04,916 --> 00:15:06,958
I know everything
about my darling.

299
00:15:07,041 --> 00:15:07,958
[gasps]

300
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:09,375
She loves being brushed.

301
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:12,416
Especially on her tummy.
Isn't that right, sweetheart?

302
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:15,250
She's got this adorable
heart-shaped spot on her belly

303
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:17,791
that she likes tickled at
the end of the day.

304
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,333
Ooh! Look, Look!

305
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:21,041
[NAPALM whines]

306
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:22,416
It's our favorite game!

307
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:25,875
We play it every night
'cause she's my dog.

308
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:31,083
Now. If we're done here,
I'd like to be on my way.

309
00:15:34,791 --> 00:15:36,291
[MILES]
Okay. Fine.

310
00:15:36,375 --> 00:15:42,041
[laughs] Come on, pumpkin.
We should get you home.

311
00:15:42,125 --> 00:15:43,583
[MISSILE whimpers]

312
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:45,583
[NAPALM whines]

313
00:15:48,958 --> 00:15:52,583
[GOLDY] Stupid kid. Now that
reward money is all mine.

314
00:15:52,666 --> 00:15:56,083
[GOLDY singing Signal Samurai]
♪ O-O-Oh. Olde Tokyo. ♪

315
00:15:56,166 --> 00:15:57,583
Hold it!

316
00:15:57,666 --> 00:15:58,958
[gasps]

317
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,666
One more thing.
That theme song...

318
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:02,916
Are you a fan?

319
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,833
I'm sorry, what do you mean?

320
00:16:04,916 --> 00:16:07,125
[MILES] Do you know
the TV show it's from?

321
00:16:07,208 --> 00:16:10,375
Um, maybe. It just happened
to pop into my head.

322
00:16:12,416 --> 00:16:13,458
[MILES]
Actually, there's something

323
00:16:13,541 --> 00:16:15,041
I've heard said before.

324
00:16:15,125 --> 00:16:17,083
That there are no such
things as coincidences

325
00:16:17,166 --> 00:16:18,708
or random occurrences.

326
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:21,000
[GOLDY]
Huh? What are you talking about?

327
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:23,416
Our actions are never
completely random.

328
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,916
Everything we do,
we do for a reason.

329
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,541
It's almost the same
color as your vest!

330
00:16:28,625 --> 00:16:31,041
For example, the song
you were singing.

331
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:33,416
You may think it came to
your mind out of nowhere.

332
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,416
But I don't believe in chance.

333
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:38,958
What I'm thinking is,
you heard it recently.

334
00:16:39,041 --> 00:16:40,083
[gasps]

335
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:41,958
[DEE] Anyway, here's
a special request.

336
00:16:42,041 --> 00:16:44,458
[Signal Samurai theme plays]

337
00:16:44,541 --> 00:16:45,708
Just like me.

338
00:16:45,791 --> 00:16:47,916
You heard the song playing
a few minutes ago.

339
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,333
--On the radio.
--[gasps]

340
00:16:49,416 --> 00:16:50,666
What's more...

341
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:53,583
...at about the same time,
the DJ had some news.

342
00:16:53,666 --> 00:16:55,541
That whoever found this
poor lost dog would be

343
00:16:55,625 --> 00:16:57,375
rewarded handsomely.

344
00:16:57,458 --> 00:16:59,750
She even mentioned that
heart-shaped spot on her belly.

345
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:02,041
Wait. I have no idea
what you're talking about.

346
00:17:02,125 --> 00:17:03,166
I heard nothing.

347
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:05,166
Then how'd the
song get in your head?

348
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:07,416
Oh, I remember now.
Yeah, it was on TV earlier.

349
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:10,125
It's the theme song
to a children's TV show.

350
00:17:10,208 --> 00:17:12,958
And before, you said
you didn't have any kids.

351
00:17:13,041 --> 00:17:15,000
Well. It's a popular
enough tune.

352
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:16,208
I'm sure it was on in a store.

353
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:17,833
[MILES]
Objection!

354
00:17:17,916 --> 00:17:19,416
[GOLDY gasps]

355
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:23,333
I hate to break it you,
but that would be impossible.

356
00:17:23,416 --> 00:17:25,208
What? How come?

357
00:17:25,291 --> 00:17:27,416
[MILES]
Because... <i>Signal Samurai</i> ...

358
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,708
...has been off the air
for three full years.

359
00:17:29,791 --> 00:17:32,083
[GOLDY wails]

360
00:17:32,166 --> 00:17:33,416
[NAPALM whines]

361
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:34,791
Just admit it,

362
00:17:34,875 --> 00:17:37,875
you were listening to the
same station I was.

363
00:17:37,958 --> 00:17:40,083
Who the hell do you
think you are, brat?

364
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:42,416
Don't you know not
to question your elders?

365
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,458
If you really are
the owner of that dog,

366
00:17:44,541 --> 00:17:46,250
aren't you forgetting something?

367
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:48,416
Huh? What do you mean?

368
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,291
Five thousand dollars.

369
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:51,083
[gasps]

370
00:17:51,166 --> 00:17:53,041
I found Napalm for you.

371
00:17:53,125 --> 00:17:56,208
Which means...
you owe me a reward.

372
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:58,458
[GOLDY growls]

373
00:17:58,541 --> 00:18:01,583
[MILES]
If you want to take her home.

374
00:18:01,666 --> 00:18:03,541
You'll have to pay me first.

375
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:06,375
[GOLDY growls]

376
00:18:06,458 --> 00:18:09,166
[bellows]

377
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:14,500
[GOLDY] You don't get to tell
a woman like me what to do.

378
00:18:14,583 --> 00:18:18,250
Hand over that
mutt and scram, kid!

379
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:20,000
That's enough!

380
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:21,041
[GOLDY]
Huh?!

381
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:24,291
Your scheming
ends here. Be gone.

382
00:18:24,375 --> 00:18:26,208
Hey. Who are you?

383
00:18:26,291 --> 00:18:27,291
You can't just--

384
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:29,583
[KARMA]
Oh. Can't I?

385
00:18:29,666 --> 00:18:32,500
Would you like to
present your case again?

386
00:18:32,583 --> 00:18:35,833
--In court, this time?
--[whip lashing]

387
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:37,541
[FRANZISKA]
Hmph.

388
00:18:37,625 --> 00:18:41,875
[GOLDY whines]
No. I won't go back to prison!

389
00:18:41,958 --> 00:18:43,375
[sobs]

390
00:18:43,458 --> 00:18:47,791
[FRANZISKA] Miles. We've been
looking all over for you.

391
00:18:47,875 --> 00:18:49,916
I apologize for
causing you trouble.

392
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:57,000
Let's go. I imagine the
pancakes must be ready by now.

393
00:18:57,083 --> 00:18:59,083
Yummy! Come on!

394
00:19:06,291 --> 00:19:09,041
[FRANZISKA sighs]
I had so much fun today.

395
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:11,875
[VOLUNTEER] Please spare
some change for these pups!

396
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:13,333
You can change a life!

397
00:19:14,041 --> 00:19:17,791
[MILES] Sir. If I receive
the reward money,

398
00:19:17,875 --> 00:19:20,208
can I donate it to
this animal shelter?

399
00:19:20,291 --> 00:19:21,333
Really?

400
00:19:21,416 --> 00:19:23,208
[VOLUNTEER]
Got some change to spare?

401
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:25,541
--Save a dog!
--Please, sir.

402
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,583
You're the one
who found the dog.

403
00:19:29,666 --> 00:19:31,833
Do as you wish.

404
00:19:31,916 --> 00:19:33,166
Thank you so much!

405
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:40,791
[KARMA]
Regarding the orphanage.

406
00:19:40,875 --> 00:19:42,125
Let's table that.

407
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:47,041
[KARMA] I've been wondering
what made me adopt

408
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:49,041
that boy three years ago.

409
00:19:49,125 --> 00:19:52,333
When he was so hurt
over the loss of his father.

410
00:19:52,416 --> 00:19:55,416
And I think today,
I finally began to understand

411
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:58,583
how we ended up
in this situation.

412
00:19:58,666 --> 00:20:00,708
It wasn't because of my guilt.

413
00:20:00,791 --> 00:20:04,375
I simply wanted to see where
the path of pain would lead us,

414
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:06,458
and how he would
eventually develop.

415
00:20:06,541 --> 00:20:10,208
Karma has a strange
way of showing itself.

416
00:20:10,291 --> 00:20:12,708
You can wear this
from now on if you would like.

417
00:20:12,791 --> 00:20:13,791
[MILES gasps]

418
00:20:15,958 --> 00:20:18,041
[laughs]
Thanks!

419
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,708
Well, you helped
me out once again...

420
00:20:32,791 --> 00:20:33,916
...my friend.

421
00:20:38,583 --> 00:20:39,875
[gasps]

422
00:20:39,958 --> 00:20:42,583
[BUTZ] Huh? What are you
standing around for?

423
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:43,666
Let's go.

424
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:45,375
[PHOENIX]
Right! Coming.

425
00:22:17,833 --> 00:22:20,333
[MAYA] So? Did Edgeworth
really hear the song?

426
00:22:20,416 --> 00:22:21,750
How's it all end?

427
00:22:21,833 --> 00:22:22,750
Who knows?

428
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:24,958
I'm sure it found
its way to him.

429
00:22:25,041 --> 00:22:26,666
Just like our killer
ad will reach him

430
00:22:26,750 --> 00:22:28,291
and everyone else in the world.

431
00:22:28,375 --> 00:22:29,875
Uh, yeah, about that...

432
00:22:29,958 --> 00:22:32,125
Now that it's done,
how do we get it out there?

433
00:22:32,208 --> 00:22:33,541
What are you talking about?

434
00:22:33,625 --> 00:22:35,208
We'll just throw it up on
the Internet and watch it

435
00:22:35,291 --> 00:22:36,666
rack up the likes. Easy!

436
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:38,125
What are you waiting for?

437
00:22:38,208 --> 00:22:39,708
Upload it now.

438
00:22:39,791 --> 00:22:42,375
[PHOENIX] I don't know. I'm not
exactly great with computers.

439
00:22:42,458 --> 00:22:44,791
They're so... confusing.

440
00:22:44,875 --> 00:22:46,416
[MAYA hums]

441
00:22:47,958 --> 00:22:49,958
--Here goes.
--[gasps] Hold on!

442
00:22:50,041 --> 00:22:51,583
[MAYA]
And... done!

443
00:22:53,625 --> 00:22:54,958
[MAYA, PHOENIX] ♪ Call Wright
and company right away! ♪

444
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:56,500
What the heck?

445
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:59,708
Hey. You didn't tell us how
crazy Japanese law ads can be.

446
00:23:02,125 --> 00:23:03,250
[gasps]

447
00:23:16,666 --> 00:23:18,125
[sighs]

448
00:23:27,875 --> 00:23:29,416
[PHOENIX]
Objection!

449
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:32,083
Maggey, The Goddess
of Misfortune, returns!

450
00:23:32,166 --> 00:23:35,666
And, just her luck, she's been
accused of murder yet again!

451
00:23:35,750 --> 00:23:38,791
This time, the crime happened
in a fancy French restaurant,

452
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:41,416
and nobody believes
what she has to say.

453
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:43,541
[PHOENIX] But even if
everyone thinks she's guilty,

454
00:23:43,625 --> 00:23:46,208
I'm on her side!
Trust me, Maggey!

455
00:23:46,291 --> 00:23:48,625
Find the contradictions!
Believe in the truth!

456
00:23:48,708 --> 00:23:51,625
Next episode: "Recipe for
Turnabout--1st Trial"!

457
00:23:51,708 --> 00:23:52,833
Take that!

